   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context "/>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Route the input cables through the top gland plate and
connect to the input busbars (L1, L2, L3, N) and to the ground busbar
in the top entry cabinet.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <title class="- topic/title ">Front View of the Top Entry Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50kva_ups_and_top_entry_cabinet_1P_connect-cables_120mm_0000166012.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Route the output cables through the top gland plate and
connect to the output busbars (L1, L2, L3, N) and to the ground busbar
in the top entry cabinet.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only in systems with remote battery cabinet(s)</b>:
Route the battery cables from the remote battery cabinet(s) through
the top gland plate and connect to the battery busbars (+, –)
and the ground busbar in the top entry cabinet.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Route the preinstalled cables from the top entry cabinet
through the transformer cabinet (if present) and into the UPS cabinet
as shown.</cmd>
